'''PP-2000''' is a character from the Tactical SRPG ES game '''[[Girls' Frontline]]''' developed by MicaTeam and published by Digital Sky and its derivatives.

== Historical basis ==

The '''PP-2000''' (From Russian ''Pistolet Pulemyot-2000'', or Machine Pistol-2000) is a submachine gun developed by KBP Instrument Bureau of Tula, Russia sporting features of both submachineguns and personal defence weapons alike, capable of firing a multitude of 9x19mm cartridges, including the Russian-developed 7N21 and 7N31 +P+ rounds.

===Specifications===
*Overall weight: 1.4 kg empty
*Overall length: 555mm / 340mm (Stock extended/retracted)
*Width: 34mm
*Overall height: 185mm (with 20-round detachable magazine) / 305mm (with 44-round detachable magazine)
*Cartridge: 9×19mm Luger, 9×19mm 7N21 +P+, 9x19mm 7N31 +P+
*Caliber: 9 mm
*Action: Direct blowback, closed bolt
*Rate of Fire: 600—800 RPM
*Muzzle velocity: 460—600min／s (7N31)
*Effective range: 100m (9x19mm Luger) / 200m (7N31)
*Feed system: 20 / 44-round detachable magazine发可拆卸式弹匣
*Sights: Mechanical sights, fixed flip-up notch and post with MIL-STD-1913 tactical rail for optics.

