The PP-2000 is an advanced submachinegun developed in Russia with features of machine pistols and personal defence weapons.

The PP-2000 is designed as a dual-purpose personal defence/close-quarters combat weapon for SWAT teams and special forces. Therefore it has a compact layout, minimalizing size while being more reliable, easy to maintain and capable of outputting strong firepower, at the same time being a close-quarters combat weapon and the sidearm of VIPs instead of a weapon for ordinary infantry.

It was officially adopted by the Russian police in 2008 alongside the PP-19-01 "Vityaz" as its standard-issue SMG.

